tweet_raw: #Bitcoin breaks 50K ETFs are having an effect.Weve all been here before. Bulls and bears rises and dips.This one is different. These are deep pockets that wont panic as easily.What we saw in other bull markets was massive hype built on nothing. People jumping in to get rich as the green candles kept coming.A lot of those people were betting their wages and small savings on the price rising so when we hit a few big bumps they started to panic and sell.Then as the markets turned even more panicked and sold compounding the downturn.According to coindesk the top three ETFs hold almost 700000 Bitcoin with huge money coming in from investors every day to get a share.Thats over 3% of the total supply taken up from just one month of activity. This is always going to have an effect on the price and these are funds that are not afraid of a few dips.They wouldnt have gotten involved in Bitcoin if they didnt see money to be made and a long term future.There are still plenty ups and downs left in the game but I think the buying pressure out there now will soak up any dips down to 30K and swallow them right back up.Where there used to be fear these big investors will see opportunity.As much as we want to see the crazy alt markets of 2019 I dont think that we will.These funds have no interest in shitcoins. The people who made their bags in the last bullruns have been shaken out of bitcoin by now and a lot of that money has been diluted down over the years across all of the different coins.There is still money in the system but i think that the next wave of successful altcoins will be built on solid principles. Business principles revenue generating systems and visible founders.Too many people have been stung by anon devs and future promises to quickly put more money into the void. What we had before was gambling. Now i want to see if we can build revenue streams and solid products.We all know that #hive is off the radar. The token isnt worth a huge amount and the community is overlooked but we are doing it differently.We know who is here building. We have people on the streets spreading the word. We have classes teaching people how to get involved. We have apps with revenue and plans. We have some of the best tech out there. We have connections built over years.It all depends if we can get it right or not.Stop looking at the reward pool and start bringing in money and users from the outside.Every app should be planning on their next 1000 users. Their next 1000 dollars and build from there.The more success that we can achieve for any project on Hive. The more success that we will all have.We can see where the games might have an effect and hope to see even more in the near future. See below.

tweet_text: staking eth on ethereum may require a banking license in switzerland while staking ada on cardano does not  the difference is in custodial vs noncustodial staking  cardanos liquid staking seems a more suitable solution not only for decentralization but also from the point of view of regulations  what is liquid staking   cardano does not define a minimum number of coins that users need for staking they therefore do not need to look for a third party that would stake coins from multiple users   cardano has no lockup periods ada coins can be spent at any time during staking   cardano doesnt have slashing users may not receive rewards if the pool misses opportunities to mint blocks they will never lose their ada if they keep them in their own wallet   delegating ada coins to a pool is very easy it only requires a few clicks in the wallet it can be a light wallet you can then close the wallet  some regulators seem to distinguish between direct staking and staking through a third party   they also distinguish whether the coins can be spent at any time or whether the system requires locking and slashing  when staking through a third party users must send coins such as eth to a custodian a custodian is a central entity that is responsible for users coins   users usually get liquid tokens that have the same price as coins but that have no role in the consensus   if the custodian carries out staking on its own account crypto assets cannot be segregated in the event of bankruptcy and trigger capital requirements for banks  why does ethereum require custodians   to run the validator you need to own 32 eth 85k usd   if users have less eth they usually look for a third party these are either centralized exchanges or projects like lido these entities represent counterparty risk   ethereum has slashing can confiscate staked coins and therefore it is necessary to lock eth users cannot spend staked eth immediately   running a validator from home requires technical knowledge a reliable internet connection and an uninterrupted power source  this type of regulation in switzerland is similar to the sec crackdown on exchanges in the us  the problem is that if cex for example goes bankrupt eth can be confiscated to pay debts to creditors  it appears that thirdparty staking will be regulated in many countries  it is surprising how well regulators understand the details of pos consensus and decentralization  cardano is more decentralized than ethereum due to liquid staking  vitalik indirectly admitted that he likes liquid staking on cardano and that his project should go in the same direction its time to do it  source cmslawnowcomenealerts20
tweet_raw: Staking $ETH on Ethereum may require a banking license in Switzerland while staking $ADA on Cardano does not.The difference is in custodial vs. non-custodial staking.#Cardanos liquid staking seems a more suitable solution not only for decentralization but also from the point of view of regulations.What is liquid staking?➡️ Cardano does not define a minimum number of coins that users need for staking. They therefore do not need to look for a third party that would stake coins from multiple users.➡️ Cardano has no lockup periods. ADA coins can be spent at any time during staking.➡️ Cardano doesnt have slashing. Users may not receive rewards if the pool misses opportunities to mint blocks. They will never lose their ADA if they keep them in their own wallet.➡️ Delegating ADA coins to a pool is very easy. It only requires a few clicks in the wallet (it can be a light wallet). You can then close the wallet.Some regulators seem to distinguish between direct staking and staking through a third party. They also distinguish whether the coins can be spent at any time or whether the system requires locking and slashing.When staking through a third party users must send coins such as ETH to a custodian. A custodian is a central entity that is responsible for users coins. Users usually get liquid tokens that have the same price as coins but that have no role in the consensus. If the custodian carries out staking on its own account crypto assets cannot be segregated in the event of bankruptcy and trigger capital requirements for banks.Why does #Ethereum require custodians?➡️ To run the validator you need to own 32 ETH (~85K USD).➡️ If users have less ETH they usually look for a third party. These are either centralized exchanges or projects like Lido. These entities represent counter-party risk.➡️ Ethereum has slashing (can confiscate staked coins) and therefore it is necessary to lock ETH. Users cannot spend staked ETH immediately.➡️ Running a validator from home requires technical knowledge a reliable internet connection and an uninterrupted power source.This type of regulation in Switzerland is similar to the SEC crackdown on exchanges in the US.The problem is that if CEX for example goes bankrupt ETH can be confiscated to pay debts to creditors.It appears that third-party staking will be regulated in many countries.It is surprising how well regulators understand the details of PoS consensus and decentralization.Cardano is more decentralized than Ethereum due to liquid staking.Vitalik indirectly admitted that he likes liquid staking on Cardano and that his project should go in the same direction. Its time to do it.Source: cms-lawnow.com/en/ealerts/20…

tweet_raw: Feb 14 1990: Voyager 1 spacecraft takes this stunning photograph of the Earth suspended in the sunbeam. Carl Sagans brilliant monologue as mentioned in his 1994 book Pale Blue Dot: From this distant vantage point the Earth might not seem of any particular interest. But for us its different. Consider again that dot. Thats here. Thats home. Thats us. On it everyone you love everyone you know everyone you ever heard of every human being who ever was lived out their lives. The aggregate of our joy and suffering thousands of confident religions ideologies and economic doctrines every hunter and forager every hero and coward every creator and destroyer of civilization every king and peasant every young couple in love every mother and father hopeful child inventor and explorer every teacher of morals every corrupt politician every superstar every supreme leader every saint and sinner in the history of our species lived there – on a mote of dust suspended in a sunbeam.The Earth is a very small stage in a vast cosmic arena. Think of the rivers of blood spilled by all those generals and emperors so that in glory and triumph they could become the momentary masters of a fraction of a dot. Think of the endless cruelties visited by the inhabitants of one corner of this pixel on the scarcely distinguishable inhabitants of some other corner how frequent their misunderstandings how eager they are to kill one another how fervent their hatreds.Our posturings our imagined self-importance the delusion that we have some privileged position in the Universe are challenged by this point of pale light. Our planet is a lonely speck in the great enveloping cosmic dark. In our obscurity in all this vastness there is no hint that help will come from elsewhere to save us from ourselves.The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life. There is nowhere else at least in the near future to which our species could migrate. Visit yes. Settle not yet. Like it or not for the moment the Earth is where we make our stand.It has been said that astronomy is a humbling and character-building experience. There is perhaps no better demonstration of the folly of human conceits than this distant image of our tiny world. To me it underscores our responsibility to deal more kindly with one another and to preserve and cherish the pale blue dot the only home weve ever known.📷NASA

tweet_raw: Pale Blue Dot is a photograph of Earth taken on February 14 1990 (34 years ago #Today) by the Voyager 1 space probe from an unprecedented distance of approximately 6 billion kilometers (3.7 billion miles 40.5 AU) as part of that days Family Portrait series of images of the Solar System.This is what Carl Sagan said about the photo:«Look again at that dot. Thats here. Thats home. Thats us. On it everyone you love everyone you know everyone you ever heard of every human being who ever was lived out their lives. The aggregate of our joy and suffering thousands of confident religions ideologies and economic doctrines every hunter and forager every hero and coward every creator and destroyer of civilization every king and peasant every young couple in love every mother and father hopeful child inventor and explorer every teacher of morals every corrupt politician every superstar every supreme leader every saint and sinner in the history of our species lived there — on a mote of dust suspended in a sunbeam.The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life. There is nowhere else at least in the near future to which our species could migrate. Visit yes. Settle not yet. Like it or not for the moment the Earth is where we make our stand. It has been said that astronomy is a humbling and character-building experience. There is perhaps no better demonstration of the folly of human conceits than this distant image of our tiny world. To me it underscores our responsibility to deal more kindly with one another and to preserve and cherish the pale blue dot the only home weve ever known».

tweet_text: pale blue dot is a photograph of earth taken on february 14 1990 34 years ago today by the voyager 1 space probe from an unprecedented distance of approximately 6 billion kilometers 37 billion miles 405 au as part of that days family portrait series of images of the solar system  this is what carl sagan said about the photo  look again at that dot thats here thats home thats us on it everyone you love everyone you know everyone you ever heard of every human being who ever was lived out their lives the aggregate of our joy and suffering thousands of confident religions ideologies and economic doctrines every hunter and forager every hero and coward every creator and destroyer of civilization every king and peasant every young couple in love every mother and father hopeful child inventor and explorer every teacher of morals every corrupt politician every superstar every supreme leader every saint and sinner in the history of our species lived there  on a mote of dust suspended in a sunbeam  the earth is the only world known so far to harbor life there is nowhere else at least in the near future to which our species could migrate visit yes settle not yet like it or not for the moment the earth is where we make our stand it has been said that astronomy is a humbling and characterbuilding experience there is perhaps no better demonstration of the folly of human conceits than this distant image of our tiny world to me it underscores our responsibility to deal more kindly with one another and to preserve and cherish the pale blue dot the only home weve ever known
tweet_raw: Pale Blue Dot is a photograph of Earth taken on February 14 1990 (34 years ago #Today) by the Voyager 1 space probe from an unprecedented distance of approximately 6 billion kilometers (3.7 billion miles 40.5 AU) as part of that days Family Portrait series of images of the Solar System.This is what Carl Sagan said about the photo:«Look again at that dot. Thats here. Thats home. Thats us. On it everyone you love everyone you know everyone you ever heard of every human being who ever was lived out their lives. The aggregate of our joy and suffering thousands of confident religions ideologies and economic doctrines every hunter and forager every hero and coward every creator and destroyer of civilization every king and peasant every young couple in love every mother and father hopeful child inventor and explorer every teacher of morals every corrupt politician every superstar every supreme leader every saint and sinner in the history of our species lived there — on a mote of dust suspended in a sunbeam.The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life. There is nowhere else at least in the near future to which our species could migrate. Visit yes. Settle not yet. Like it or not for the moment the Earth is where we make our stand. It has been said that astronomy is a humbling and character-building experience. There is perhaps no better demonstration of the folly of human conceits than this distant image of our tiny world. To me it underscores our responsibility to deal more kindly with one another and to preserve and cherish the pale blue dot the only home weve ever known».

tweet_raw: 2024/02/13 ENTC NFT User Reward Event Additional AnnouncementGreetings from ENTC.In conjunction with the launch of the LIVE platform the Foundation has conducted a reward event for the ENTC NFT collection to express our gratitude to the users who have shown interest and love for our project. Due to feedback received about the short participation window during the event held from January 1 to January 10 2024 we have planned an extension of the event duration.We kindly ask for your active participation and support within the extended period and event details provided below.ENTC NFT User Reward Event (Extension)Duration: March 10 2024 00:00 (KST) - March 31 2024 23:59 (KST)Participation Method: Rewards in ETH or ENTC will be provided for returning (transferring) any ENTC NFT collection purchased through OpenSea to the Foundations issued wallet during the event period.Return Wallet Address: 0xbf255Fa575c3Fe97d16c07413126D2784d50f9Fe*Please ensure to double-check the network and address before transferring as the return wallet address and NFT ENTC are all based on the Ethereum network. Note that NFT tokens lost due to network and address entry errors will not be compensated.Reward Amount: 5 ETH or equivalent ENTC per NFT*The type of reward ETH or ENTC will be determined and disbursed based on the Total Value Locked (TVL) following the operation of the swap pool after liquidity provision to the community pool starting April 1 2024.Reward Disbursement Schedule: Sequentially disbursed from April 1 2024 with liquidity provided to the community pool*Please note that the final reward completion may take up to 90 days.*For users who have records of inquiries to cs@sdkbenter.com regarding re-participation after sending or returning the return of the NFTs sent before March 9 2024 is planned. Please ensure to select and resend within the additional event period after receiving your NFT.Thank you.—-2024/02/13 ENTC NFT 유저 보상 이벤트 추가 안내재단은 the LIVE 플랫폼 런칭과 더불어 프로젝트에 관심과 사랑을 보내주신 유저분들께 보답하고자 ENTC NFT 컬렉션에 대한 보상 이벤트를 진행하였습니다. 2024년 1월 1일 ~ 10일까지 진행된 이벤트 과정 중 참여 기간이 다소 짧다는 유저분들의 의견이 많아 이벤트 기간 추가 확장을 기획하였습니다.이에 안내 드리오니 기간과 내용을 참조하시어 많은 참여와 성원을 부탁드립니다.ENTC NFT 유저 보상 이벤트(추가)기간 : 2024년 3월 10일 00:00(KST) - 2024년 3월 31일 23:59(KST)참여 방법 : 오픈씨를 통해 구매한 ENTC NFT 컬렉션(종류 무관)을 재단 발행 지갑으로 이벤트 기간내 반납(전송)시 ETH 또는 ENTC로 보상 지급반납 지갑주소 : 0xbf255Fa575c3Fe97d16c07413126D2784d50f9Fe*반납 지갑주소 및 NFT ENTC는 모두 이더리움 네트워크 기반으로 전송시 네트워크 및 주소 재확인을 반드시 부탁드립니다. (네트워크 및 주소 기입 실수로 인한 NFT 토큰 유실은 보상하지 않음에 유의하여 주십시오)보상 지급 수량 : NFT 1개당 5 ETH 또는 이에 상응하는 ENTC*보상 지급 종류인 ETH ENTC는 2024년 4월 1일부터 시작되는 커뮤니티풀 유동성 제공 이후 스왑풀 운영에 따른 TVL(예치 잔량)에 따라 결정 지급됩니다.보상 지급 일정 : 2024년 4월 1일부터 커뮤니티풀에 제공되는 유동성으로 순차 지급*최종 보상 완료까지 최대 90일의 기간이 소요될 수 있습니다.*오전송 또는 반납 후 재참여에 대하여 cs@sdkbenter.com 문의 기록이 존재하는 유저분들께서는 2024년 3월 9일까지 전송해주신 NFT의 반납이 이루어질 예정이오니 NFT를 수령하신 후 위 추가 이벤트 기간내 반드시 선별 후 재전송을 부탁드립니다.감사합니다.
